<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,981,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">
Five males and one female were collected at the 
<collectionCode box="[703,775,982,1006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">PNSD</collectionCode>
in 
<number box="[811,866,982,1006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2011.0">2011</number>
(one male and one female), 
<number box="[1191,1247,982,1006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2013.0">2013</number>
(two males) and 
<number box="[151,207,1018,1042]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2014.0">2014</number>
(two males). In 
<number box="[398,455,1018,1042]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2011.0">2011</number>
, the male specimen was collected at the hilltop when resting under a leaf, five meters from the ground at 
<number box="[364,393,1053,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="15.0">15</number>
: 
<number box="[397,430,1053,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="30.0">30</number>
h., and in 
<date box="[537,703,1053,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2013" valueMax="2014">
<number box="[537,593,1054,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2013.0">2013</number>
and 
<number box="[647,703,1054,1078]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</date>
the males were captured about four meters from the ground while fighting in circular flight around 
<number box="[526,554,1089,1114]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="15.0">15</number>
:00h. The female was collected in 
<number box="[947,1002,1090,1114]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2011.0">2011</number>
at the base of a different hill, close to the Moa river at 
<number box="[337,366,1125,1150]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="17.0">17</number>
:00h., flying slowly one meter from the ground.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="243" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,981,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">
<taxonomicName box="[199,472,1162,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iracyi">
<emphasis box="[199,472,1162,1185]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Argyrogrammana iracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently described based on a single male collected in Santo Antônio do Tauá, Pará, 
<collectingCountry box="[216,284,1197,1222]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jauffret" box="[299,578,1197,1222]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" refString="Jauffret, P. &amp; Jauffret, J. C. (2007) Description de deux especes nouvelles de Riodinidae appartenant aux genres Zelotaea Bates, 1868 et Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932, provenant de la region de l'embouchure de l'amazone (Lepidoptera). Lambillionea, 107, 611 - 615." type="journal article" year="2007">
Jauffret &amp; Jauffret 
<number box="[517,578,1198,1222]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Apparently, the five males and one female collected at 
<collectionCode box="[1222,1294,1198,1222]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">PNSD</collectionCode>
are the only specimens known for this species excluding the 
<typeStatus box="[718,820,1233,1258]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[834,1108,1234,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iracyi">
<emphasis box="[834,1108,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Argyrogrammana iracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the wings color pattern similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[308,356,1270,1294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[395,530,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="placibilis">
<emphasis box="[395,530,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. placibilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[894,991,1270,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iracyi">
<emphasis box="[894,991,1270,1293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. iracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in several aspects, mainly by the pointed hook-like structure which connects the valvae ventrally whereas this feature is absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1429,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="placibilis">
<emphasis box="[1290,1429,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. placibilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Considering the shape of the valvae, 
<taxonomicName box="[595,870,1342,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iracyi">
<emphasis box="[595,870,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Argyrogrammana iracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman &amp; Salvin, 1886" authorityName="Godman &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[1265,1435,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. occidentalis</emphasis>
(Godman &amp; Salvin, 
<number box="[387,444,1377,1402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="1886.0">1886</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Brevignon &amp; Gallard, 1995" authorityName="Brevignon &amp; Gallard" authorityYear="1995" box="[513,971,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublimis">
<emphasis box="[513,640,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. sublimis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[651,971,1377,1402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard, 
<number box="[912,971,1377,1402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The female collected at the 
<collectionCode box="[1311,1383,1378,1402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">PNSD</collectionCode>
was paired with the males observing the similarity between the black spots of the wings, additionally, it differs from all females known for this complex figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[662,989,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number box="[923,981,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[1050,1327,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1996) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, part 2, with one new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 7, 71 - 80." type="journal article" year="1996">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number box="[1258,1319,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The two subspecies described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gallard" box="[433,604,1485,1510]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" refString="Gallard, J. - Y. (2008) Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise: Trois especes et trois sous-speces nouvelles (Lepidoptera). Lambillionea, 108, 441 - 454." type="journal article" year="2008">
Gallard (
<number box="[535,596,1486,1510]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[617,828,1485,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="iracyi" subSpecies="saulensis">
<emphasis box="[617,828,1485,1510]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. iracyi saulensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[886,1062,1486,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="iracyi" subSpecies="tunari">
<emphasis box="[886,1062,1486,1509]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">A. iracyi tunari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to a distinct species (see discussion below).
</paragraph>
